      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Cerebral Candidate</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jamie Spencer letter disagrees with Maureen Dowd June 6 Op-Ed column faulting Sen Barack Obama for his failure to use 'forceful one-liner or 'witty takedown' in presidential debates</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Can He Unleash the Force?'' (column, June 6), Maureen Dowd faults Senator Barack Obama for his failure to use a ''forceful one-liner'' or a ''witty takedown'' in the debates.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Can He Unleash the Force?'' (column, June 6), Maureen Dowd faults Senator Barack Obama for his failure to use a ''forceful one-liner'' or a ''witty takedown'' in the debates.</p>
        <p>On the other hand, perhaps some voters consider a candidate who eschews petulance and pettiness in favor of thoughtful and cerebral answers to be, well, in a word, presidential.</p>
        <p>Jamie Spencer  Austin, Tex., June 6, 2007</p>
      </block>
